  <span id="freeText17689851793995050062" style="display:none">Horror is my least favorite genre but real read horror if it's well written and The Ruins is wonderful. I loved it. I read The Simple Plan and loved the prose and the characterization between the two brothers. I thought Simple Plan would be a one and out and then The Ruins came out. I bought because of how much I loved Simple Plan and was not disappointed. I wish he would write them faster. The Ruins is more about the relationship between friends when put under extreme stress. So if you like well written horror stories grab up this one you won't be sorry.<br />David Putnam Author of The Bruno Johnson series.</span>
