<span id="freeTextContainer567301367910378129">This is horror at its finest. It&apos;s hard to believe all the negative reviews this book gets. I have 7 to 10 books that I always keep extra copies of, so when I meet a horror fan who hasn&apos;t read one of my favorites, all I have to do is grab an extra from my bookshelves and say, here, give this one a shot. I&apos;ve given away 2 copies of this book in the 10 years that it&apos;s been out, and so far everyone has loved it. Even my husband liked it, and he only reads thrillers. I have no review for this book, </span>
  <span id="freeText567301367910378129" style="display:none">This is horror at its finest. It's hard to believe all the negative reviews this book gets. I have 7 to 10 books that I always keep extra copies of, so when I meet a horror fan who hasn't read one of my favorites, all I have to do is grab an extra from my bookshelves and say, here, give this one a shot. I've given away 2 copies of this book in the 10 years that it's been out, and so far everyone has loved it. Even my husband liked it, and he only reads thrillers. I have no review for this book, because I suck at reviews. All I can say is believe the good reviews, and pay no mind to those bad ones. I've read this book 4 times, and its still a horrific read. Yep, I'd recommend this story.</span>
