<div id="review_2953642026" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2953642026" />
    <a title="Shaina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49002481-shaina"><img alt="Shaina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1596530962p2/49002481.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2953642026?book_show_action=true">Oct 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shaina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shaina" href="/user/show/49002481-shaina">Shaina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781400043873" href="/book/show/21726.The_Ruins">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=anthropology">anthropology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=have-own">have-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=horror-afficionados">horror-afficionados</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=myth-fable-origin-parable-etc">myth-fable-origin-parable-etc</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=eerie-spooky-gothic-weird-creepy">eerie-spooky-gothic-weird-creepy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=really-gross-like-nauseatingly-eyew">really-gross-like-nauseatingly-eyew</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=books-of-the-month">books-of-the-month</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=my-own-1001-book-list">my-own-1001-book-list</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=the-great-outdoors">the-great-outdoors</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2953642026" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11454752172860950917">Okay, after thinking about this book, though it was last year that I read it, I’m writing another review to replace the one that vanished. <br/>When I finished the book I was pretty angry. But I think that might have been the point. Without exactly giving anything away, you are led through this entire trip with some kids on vacation. Post- high school or college age kids... wandering around in Mexico somewhere or on an island; they get big ideas. And do you think any of them spoke Spanish or decided </span>
  <span id="freeText11454752172860950917" style="display:none">Okay, after thinking about this book, though it was last year that I read it, I’m writing another review to replace the one that vanished. <br />When I finished the book I was pretty angry. But I think that might have been the point. Without exactly giving anything away, you are led through this entire trip with some kids on vacation. Post- high school or college age kids... wandering around in Mexico somewhere or on an island; they get big ideas. And do you think any of them spoke Spanish or decided to get a guide when they decided to wander off into the jungle and find some ancient ruins ? No. I kept saying “You idiots!” Never go wandering off in a JUNGLE in a place you don’t understand. Mistake number one. <br /><br />They just kinda have an idea where this ruin is. Oh, someone, someone please. These poor idiots. This is jungle. They hop in the back of some guy’s truck and he takes them as far as he can but he tells them, three or four times, don’t go there... it’s BAD! They run into a native tribe. They of course try to get directions. No one will speak about it. <br /><br />How many hints do these idiots need!!! This was driving me crazy by this point but, yes, for the rest of the book to take place they have to be stupid enough to get there. So... <br /><br />Long story short .. a man catches them about to step out into a clearing that divides the ruin from the rest of the land. He is seriously trying to stop them! There is one in the group taking pictures. You’d think she’d cool it but, no. <br /> <br />She trips over a flowery vine in her picture taking idiocy and suddenly he is shoving them all toward the ruin instead of trying to keep them away! <br />Now it’s the opposite. The tribesmen guard them and keep them on the hill, with the ruin, with the indication they will be killed if they come down. <br />Why ? <br />Oh .. they slowly (way too slowly) figure it out. <br />The Indians know the evil that resides on that ruin and they want to keep it there. <br />They start trying to figure out how to survive until they are missed though no one knows of this side venture and a way to get past the guardians and escape. But they don’t realize they have far worse problems right there with them. <br /><br />The villain, the evil, the entity in this story is the genius part. The characters drive me crazy except for one. <br />The predatory evil in this book is why it gets rated so high. It’s why it’s rounded up to 4. It is what made every page of frustrating character dialogue and idiocy worth it. <br /><br />3.5 rounded up</span>
  <a data-text-id="11454752172860950917" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


