              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=nook-or-ebook">nook-or-ebook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=eerie-spooky-gothic-weird-creepy">eerie-spooky-gothic-weird-creepy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=have-own">have-own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=books-of-the-month">books-of-the-month</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=2018">2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=archaeology">archaeology</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=my-own-1001-book-list">my-own-1001-book-list</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=the-great-outdoors">the-great-outdoors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49002481-shaina?shelf=review-of-the-year">review-of-the-year</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1886919395" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2524023208056343907">3.5 ⭐️This book started out in an odd way and with what felt like, to me was a rocky tone. It just starts telling you random bits of things, spitting them at you and in random order. Maybe we were supposed to feel like (stereotypical) disorganized and ignorant college kids that had gotten drunk on the beach the night before ? Maybe. If so, that was effective. <br/><br/>I kept telling myself, okay, it will settle eventually into an individual’s point of view; or become at least somewhat more coherent and s</span>
  <span id="freeText2524023208056343907" style="display:none">3.5 ⭐️This book started out in an odd way and with what felt like, to me was a rocky tone. It just starts telling you random bits of things, spitting them at you and in random order. Maybe we were supposed to feel like (stereotypical) disorganized and ignorant college kids that had gotten drunk on the beach the night before ? Maybe. If so, that was effective. <br /><br />I kept telling myself, okay, it will settle eventually into an individual’s point of view; or become at least somewhat more coherent and showy, rather than spitting it out and telling me in such a random way. <br />I kept going and I gave it a chance. It does settle down somewhat with the fact spitting, and just starts to tell the story more by trying to open the door for the reader and let them in, but it’s not too good at it. <br />It is a tension filled novel and maybe that is why it was written like this in such a jolting manner. It became smoother, but still I could see it being so much better if the characters were fleshed out more and made a bit more likable. Some parts of all of them were a bit likable, you know, what was there. There wasn’t much depth allowed, it seemed. I think that should be part of the horror, ie; being attached to a character that you get to know and appreciate that fights so hard only to perhaps be the one to die suddenly. Perhaps not! <br /><br />This book did hold my attention and I liked Jeff because he was smart and he and Matthias made a good team. But I almost feel like even he had a case of the stupids at a time or two. But it was a bad situation. My gosh just ugh !! I’m frustrated with the characters. You are in Cancún and staying there for a number of weeks. It’s just Spanish. You can’t learn the important phrases? Or like why not sit with Dora the explorer a few times ! I could understand Mayan somehow even though I just knew Spanish so I’m not sure what the deal was there. Mayan-Spanish ... I digress.<br /><br />So, all in all, pretty unsettling story I will say, but has some irksome things about it. The entity part was very unsettling and interesting. So freaky. So so freaky. It made reading through some of the spacey characters thoughts and getting through some of the choppiness in the beginning worth it. I enjoyed and was freaked out by it. One thing needed. Fire.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2524023208056343907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


