  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1689565015" />
    <a title="Richard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8386404-richard"><img alt="Richard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1351707681p2/8386404.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1689565015?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Richard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Richard" href="/user/show/8386404-richard">Richard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8700070-the-ruins">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8386404-richard?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1689565015" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10295664172249403945">7.5/10<br/><br/>Not as enjoyable as his other book, “A Simple Plan” but still an interesting read overall. Why won’t this guy write a little quicker? Two books in over a decade isn’t prolific enough for my liking, especially when they&apos;re this good!!! Do what I demand and write more! <br/><br/>This is a complete change in style to his other book, this is more horror of the human vs. nature type but also the horrors of being a human and the choices we have to make in certain situations. The characters are flawed and </span>
  <span id="freeText10295664172249403945" style="display:none">7.5/10<br /><br />Not as enjoyable as his other book, “A Simple Plan” but still an interesting read overall. Why won’t this guy write a little quicker? Two books in over a decade isn’t prolific enough for my liking, especially when they're this good!!! Do what I demand and write more! <br /><br />This is a complete change in style to his other book, this is more horror of the human vs. nature type but also the horrors of being a human and the choices we have to make in certain situations. The characters are flawed and I liked that about them. They end up making some hugely idiotic choices. <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[At one point I was thinking they should be more like Jeff and practical about their situation but then I realised I would probably drown my sorrows in tequila and ruin any chance of survival just like them. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /><br />It took a bit for me to get into this one, probably down to not having much chance to read it early on. The characters were easily interchangeable until things really got underway about 1/3 of the way through. They all found their own voice from then on and I liked the switching of perspectives along the way. It was a fun read, in the disturbing kind of way, with some pretty horrific/graphic moments by the end. <br /><br />Well worth a read, not one for the overly squeamish and give it a chance early on without too much judgement on the knobhead characters and you’re in for a fun ride. I can’t wait to pick up Scott B. Smith’s next novel when I’m in the nursing home. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10295664172249403945" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

